div.p:
"You are main sharp upon me, lad," said Mrs. Withers, looking at him earnestly;
                     "but I was in the wrong, I take it, and spoke hasty like. It's because I love
                     the lass so well—and good cause have I to do so—that I can't bear to hear a
                     word of our parting. But I feared she might not be easy to stop along with us;
                     for she's a spirit of her own, has Elinor, and ways of her own too, that I
                     never could justly fathom, though I have reared young ones myself."
